  <brief_title>A Study to Compare the Conversion to Prograf速 (Tacrolimus) to the Continuation of Cyclosporine in Patients at Risk for Chronic Renal Allograft Failure</brief_title>
  <acronym>CRAF</acronym>
  <official_title>Prograf速 (Tacrolimus) as Secondary Intervention vs. Continuation of Cyclosporine in Patients at Risk for Chronic Renal Allograft Failure</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Astellas Pharma Inc</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Astellas Pharma Inc</source>
  <oversight_info>
    <has_dmc>Yes</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      A study to compare the conversion to Prograf速 (tacrolimus) to the continuation of
      cyclosporine in patients at risk for chronic renal allograft failure
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      A two arm study (1 Active, 1 Active control) to compare the incidence, progression and
      severity of chronic renal allograft failure in at-risk patients who are converted from
      cyclosporine-based to tacrolimus-based immunosuppression to patients who remain on
      cyclosporine-based therapy
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
